 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\"display_name\": \"Python 3\", \"language\": \"python\", \"name\": \"python3\"},\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\"name\": \"python\", \"version\": \"3.11.0\"}\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Credit Card Default Prediction\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Classification Project 4 of 100** — Predict whether a credit card client will default on next month's payment.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"End-to-end workflow: EDA → preprocessing → baseline → LazyPredict → FLAML → top 3 evaluation.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 2. Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Credit card default is a critical risk management problem in consumer banking. When a cardholder fails to make the minimum payment, the bank faces financial loss and must allocate reserves.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"In this notebook we build a **binary classifier** that predicts whether a client will default next month (`default.payment.next.month = 1`) using 23 features covering demographics, credit limit, payment history, bill statements, and previous payments from the UCI *Default of Credit Card Clients* dataset.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Workflow:**\\n\", \"1. Download & validate the dataset from Kaggle\\n\", \"2. Perform thorough EDA with visualisations\\n\", \"3. Preprocess with sklearn pipelines (split-before-fit, no leakage)\\n\", \"4. Establish baselines (Dummy, LogReg, Random Forest)\\n\", \"5. Benchmark ~30 classifiers with LazyPredict\\n\", \"6. Run FLAML AutoML\\n\", \"7. Select & evaluate the top 3 models with full metrics\\n\", \"8. Analyse errors and extract business insights\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 3. Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"By completing this notebook you will learn to:\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Work with a **moderately imbalanced credit dataset** (~22% default rate)\\n\", \"2. Handle **PAY_x repayment status codes** (including undocumented -2, -1, 0 values)\\n\", \"3. Engineer features from **payment-to-bill ratios** and **utilisation rates**\\n\", \"4. Build a **leakage-free** preprocessing pipeline with `ColumnTransformer`\\n\", \"5. Choose appropriate metrics when **false negatives** (missed defaults) are costly\\n\", \"6. Use **DummyClassifier** as the essential sanity-check baseline\\n\", \"7. Benchmark with **LazyPredict** and tune with **FLAML**\\n\", \"8. Evaluate with **accuracy, F1, precision, recall, ROC-AUC, PR-AUC, confusion matrix**\\n\", \"9. Extract **actionable risk insights** about education, marriage, and payment behaviour\\n\", \"10. Understand the **business cost** of under-predicting vs over-predicting default\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 4. Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Given a credit card client's demographics, credit limit, six months of repayment status, bill amounts, and payment amounts, predict whether they will default on next month's payment.**\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This is a **binary classification** task with moderate imbalance (~22% default). Missing a default (false negative) has higher cost than a false alarm, making **recall** and **PR-AUC** important metrics alongside accuracy and F1.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 5. Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Stakeholder | Impact |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Banks** | Reduce credit losses by identifying risky accounts early |\\n\", \"| **Risk teams** | Allocate capital reserves more accurately |\\n\", \"| **Collection departments** | Prioritise outreach to high-risk clients |\\n\", \"| **Regulators** | Ensure lending practices are sound and data-driven |\\n\", \"| **ML learners** | Practice handling imbalanced data, repayment-status encoding, and multi-metric evaluation |\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 6. Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Name** | Default of Credit Card Clients |\\n\", \"| **Source** | UCI ML Repository / Kaggle |\\n\", \"| **Kaggle slug** | `uciml/default-of-credit-card-clients-dataset` |\\n\", \"| **Rows** | 30,000 |\\n\", \"| **Features** | 23 (demographics, credit limit, 6-month payment history) |\\n\", \"| **Target** | `default.payment.next.month` (0 = no default, 1 = default) |\\n\", \"| **Class balance** | ~78% no default, ~22% default |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Key columns:**\\n\", \"- `LIMIT_BAL` — credit limit\\n\", \"- `SEX`, `EDUCATION`, `MARRIAGE`, `AGE` — demographics\\n\", \"- `PAY_0` to `PAY_6` — repayment status (months Sep to Apr)\\n\", \"- `BILL_AMT1`–`BILL_AMT6` — monthly bill amounts\\n\", \"- `PAY_AMT1`–`PAY_AMT6` — monthly payment amounts\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 7. Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- **Original source:** Yeh, I. C., & Lien, C. H. (2009). *The comparisons of data mining techniques for the predictive accuracy of probability of default of credit card clients*. Expert Systems with Applications, 36(2), 2473-2480.\\n\", \"- **UCI Repository:** https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/default+of+credit+card+clients\\n\", \"- **Kaggle:** https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/uciml/default-of-credit-card-clients-dataset\\n\", \"- **License:** CC BY 4.0 — free for educational and commercial use with attribution.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 8. Environment Setup\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We install any packages not already available.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"\\n\", \"for pkg in [\\\"lazypredict\\\", \\\"flaml\\\", \\\"kagglehub\\\"]:\\n\", \"    try:\\n\", \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\", \"    except ImportError:\\n\", \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 9. Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import os, warnings, json, glob\\n\", \"import numpy as np\\n\", \"import pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\", \"import seaborn as sns\\n\", \"\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\\n\", \"from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\n\", \"from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (\\n\", \"    accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\\n\", \"    roc_auc_score, average_precision_score, confusion_matrix,\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay, RocCurveDisplay, PrecisionRecallDisplay,\\n\", \"    classification_report\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyClassifier\\n\", \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\", \"\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\", \"sns.set_theme(style=\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"print(\\\"All imports loaded.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 10. Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"KAGGLE_SLUG = \\\"uciml/default-of-credit-card-clients-dataset\\\"\\n\", \"TARGET = \\\"default.payment.next.month\\\"\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.15\\n\", \"VAL_SIZE = 0.15\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"FLAML_BUDGET = 120  # seconds\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Target: {TARGET} | Test: {TEST_SIZE} | Seed: {SEED}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 11. Dataset Download or Loading\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We use `kagglehub` to download the dataset. Kaggle credentials must be available via the `KAGGLE_API_TOKEN` environment variable or `~/.kaggle/kaggle.json`.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import kagglehub\\n\", \"\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    path = kagglehub.dataset_download(KAGGLE_SLUG)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Dataset downloaded to: {path}\\\")\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    raise RuntimeError(\\n\", \"        f\\\"Failed to download dataset: {e}\\\\n\\\"\\n\", \"        \\\"Ensure KAGGLE_API_TOKEN is set or ~/.kaggle/kaggle.json exists.\\\"\\n\", \"    )\\n\", \"\\n\", \"csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path, \\\"**\\\", \\\"*.csv\\\"), recursive=True)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"CSV files found: {csv_files}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"df_raw = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"df_raw.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 12. Data Validation Checks\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We verify data integrity: correct shape, expected columns, missing values, duplicates, and target distribution.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nMissing values: {df_raw.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Drop ID column if present\\n\", \"if \\\"ID\\\" in df_raw.columns:\\n\", \"    df = df_raw.drop(columns=[\\\"ID\\\"]).copy()\\n\", \"    print(\\\"Dropped ID column.\\\")\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    df = df_raw.copy()\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dupes = df.duplicated().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Duplicate rows: {dupes}\\\")\\n\", \"if dupes > 0:\\n\", \"    df = df.drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"After dedup: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"assert TARGET in df.columns, f\\\"Target column {TARGET} not found!\\\"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTarget distribution:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Default rate: {df[TARGET].mean():.3f}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 13. Exploratory Data Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We explore distributions, correlations, and relationships with the target.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"df.describe().T\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(5, 4))\\n\", \"df[TARGET].value_counts().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=[\\\"steelblue\\\", \\\"salmon\\\"])\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Target Distribution\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_xticklabels([\\\"No Default\\\", \\\"Default\\\"], rotation=0)\\n\", \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Count\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"numeric_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"corr = df[numeric_cols].corr()[TARGET].drop(TARGET).sort_values(key=abs, ascending=False)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Top correlations with target:\\\")\\n\", \"print(corr.head(15))\\n\", \"\\n\", \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 10))\\n\", \"sns.heatmap(df[numeric_cols].corr(), cmap=\\\"coolwarm\\\", center=0, ax=ax, fmt=\\\".1f\\\", linewidths=0.5)\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Feature Correlation Matrix\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\", \"for i, col in enumerate([\\\"PAY_0\\\", \\\"LIMIT_BAL\\\"]):\\n\", \"    for label, grp in df.groupby(TARGET):\\n\", \"        tag = \\\"Default\\\" if label == 1 else \\\"No Default\\\"\\n\", \"        axes[i].hist(grp[col], bins=30, alpha=0.5, label=tag)\\n\", \"    axes[i].set_title(f\\\"{col} by Default Status\\\")\\n\", \"    axes[i].legend()\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 14. Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"The target has ~22% positive (default) class — moderate imbalance. A majority-class-only model achieves ~78% accuracy but 0% recall.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"default_rate = df[TARGET].mean()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Default rate: {default_rate:.1%}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Majority-class baseline accuracy: {1 - default_rate:.1%}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Class counts:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Imbalance ratio: {(1-default_rate)/default_rate:.1f}:1\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 15. Train / Validation / Test Split Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We use a **70/15/15 stratified** split. We split **before** any preprocessing to prevent data leakage.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET])\\n\", \"y = df[TARGET]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"X_temp, X_test, y_temp, y_test = train_test_split(\\n\", \"    X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y\\n\", \")\\n\", \"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(\\n\", \"    X_temp, y_temp, test_size=VAL_SIZE / (1 - TEST_SIZE),\\n\", \"    random_state=SEED, stratify=y_temp\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Train: {X_train.shape}  Val: {X_val.shape}  Test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"for name, ys in [(\\\"Train\\\", y_train), (\\\"Val\\\", y_val), (\\\"Test\\\", y_test)]:\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"{name} default rate: {ys.mean():.3f}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 16. Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Decisions:**\\n\", \"- **Missing values:** None in this dataset.\\n\", \"- **PAY_x codes:** -2, -1, 0 alongside 1-9. Trees handle this natively.\\n\", \"- **Scaling:** StandardScaler for logistic regression compatibility.\\n\", \"- **No leakage:** ColumnTransformer fit only on training data.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"feature_cols = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(\\n\", \"    transformers=[(\\\"scale\\\", StandardScaler(), feature_cols)],\\n\", \"    remainder=\\\"passthrough\\\"\\n\", \")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Features: {len(feature_cols)}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 17. Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We create domain-inspired features:\\n\", \"- **AVG_PAY_STATUS / MAX_PAY_STATUS** — average and worst repayment delay\\n\", \"- **PAY_BILL_RATIO** — total payments / total bills\\n\", \"- **UTIL_RATIO** — most recent bill / credit limit\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"def engineer_features(df_in):\\n\", \"    df_out = df_in.copy()\\n\", \"    pay_status_cols = [c for c in [\\\"PAY_0\\\",\\\"PAY_2\\\",\\\"PAY_3\\\",\\\"PAY_4\\\",\\\"PAY_5\\\",\\\"PAY_6\\\"]\\n\", \"                       if c in df_out.columns]\\n\", \"    if pay_status_cols:\\n\", \"        df_out[\\\"AVG_PAY_STATUS\\\"] = df_out[pay_status_cols].mean(axis=1)\\n\", \"        df_out[\\\"MAX_PAY_STATUS\\\"] = df_out[pay_status_cols].max(axis=1)\\n\", \"    bill_cols = [f\\\"BILL_AMT{i}\\\" for i in range(1, 7) if f\\\"BILL_AMT{i}\\\" in df_out.columns]\\n\", \"    pay_amt_cols = [f\\\"PAY_AMT{i}\\\" for i in range(1, 7) if f\\\"PAY_AMT{i}\\\" in df_out.columns]\\n\", \"    if bill_cols and pay_amt_cols:\\n\", \"        total_bill = df_out[bill_cols].sum(axis=1).clip(lower=1)\\n\", \"        total_pay = df_out[pay_amt_cols].sum(axis=1)\\n\", \"        df_out[\\\"PAY_BILL_RATIO\\\"] = total_pay / total_bill\\n\", \"    if \\\"LIMIT_BAL\\\" in df_out.columns and bill_cols:\\n\", \"        df_out[\\\"UTIL_RATIO\\\"] = df_out[bill_cols[0]] / df_out[\\\"LIMIT_BAL\\\"].clip(lower=1)\\n\", \"    return df_out\\n\", \"\\n\", \"X_train = engineer_features(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val = engineer_features(X_val)\\n\", \"X_test = engineer_features(X_test)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"new_feats = [c for c in X_train.columns if c not in feature_cols]\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Engineered features: {new_feats}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Total features: {X_train.shape[1]}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"all_features = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(\\n\", \"    transformers=[(\\\"scale\\\", StandardScaler(), all_features)],\\n\", \"    remainder=\\\"passthrough\\\"\\n\", \")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 18. Baseline Model\\n\", \"\\n\", \"DummyClassifier sets the floor, then LogReg and Random Forest.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"results = {}\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dummy = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", DummyClassifier(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\", random_state=SEED))])\\n\", \"dummy.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"y_pred_d = dummy.predict(X_val)\\n\", \"results[\\\"Dummy\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred_d), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, y_pred_d), \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_val, y_pred_d)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"Dummy:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"Dummy\\\"].items()})\\n\", \"\\n\", \"lr = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED))])\\n\", \"lr.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"y_prob_lr = lr.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"LogReg\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)),\\n\", \"                     \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_lr)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"LogReg:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"LogReg\\\"].items()})\\n\", \"\\n\", \"rf = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED, n_jobs=-1))])\\n\", \"rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"y_prob_rf = rf.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"RF\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)),\\n\", \"                 \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_rf)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"RF:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"RF\\\"].items()})\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 19. LazyPredict Benchmark\\n\", \"\\n\", \"LazyPredict fits ~30 classifiers quickly. This is for **exploration only**.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_lp = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val_lp = preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"lazy = LazyClassifier(verbose=0, ignore_warnings=True, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"models_lp, _ = lazy.fit(X_train_lp, X_val_lp, y_train, y_val)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Top 15 models by Accuracy:\\\")\\n\", \"models_lp.head(15)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 20. FLAML AutoML Run\\n\", \"\\n\", \"FLAML optimises for **F1** given the class imbalance.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"automl = AutoML()\\n\", \"automl.fit(\\n\", \"    X_train, y_train,\\n\", \"    task=\\\"classification\\\",\\n\", \"    metric=\\\"f1\\\",\\n\", \"    time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,\\n\", \"    seed=SEED,\\n\", \"    verbose=0,\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best model: {automl.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best config: {automl.best_config}\\\")\\n\", \"y_pred_fl = automl.predict(X_val)\\n\", \"y_prob_fl = automl.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"FLAML\\\"] = {\\n\", \"    \\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred_fl),\\n\", \"    \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, y_pred_fl),\\n\", \"    \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_val, y_pred_fl),\\n\", \"    \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_fl),\\n\", \"    \\\"PR-AUC\\\": average_precision_score(y_val, y_prob_fl),\\n\", \"}\\n\", \"print(\\\"FLAML:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"FLAML\\\"].items()})\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 21. Top 3 Model Selection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Based on LazyPredict and FLAML results, we select three gradient-boosting families:\\n\", \"1. **LightGBM** — typically top for tabular data\\n\", \"2. **XGBoost** — strong alternative\\n\", \"3. **GradientBoosting** — sklearn ensemble\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"try:\\n\", \"    from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier\\n\", \"    has_lgbm = True\\n\", \"except ImportError:\\n\", \"    has_lgbm = False\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    from xgboost import XGBClassifier\\n\", \"    has_xgb = True\\n\", \"except ImportError:\\n\", \"    has_xgb = False\\n\", \"\\n\", \"top3 = {}\\n\", \"if has_lgbm:\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"LightGBM\\\"] = LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=500, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=6, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED, verbose=-1, n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"ExtraTrees\\\"] = ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=500, class_weight=\\\"balanced\\\", random_state=SEED, n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"if has_xgb:\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"XGBoost\\\"] = XGBClassifier(n_estimators=500, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=6, scale_pos_weight=(y_train==0).sum()/(y_train==1).sum(), random_state=SEED, verbosity=0, n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"AdaBoost\\\"] = AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"top3[\\\"GradientBoosting\\\"] = GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=300, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=5, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top 3: {list(top3.keys())}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 22. Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Train on full training set, evaluate on held-out test set.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_t = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val_t = preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"X_test_t = preprocessor.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"final_results = {}\\n\", \"for name, model in top3.items():\\n\", \"    model.fit(X_train_t, y_train)\\n\", \"    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_t)\\n\", \"    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test_t)[:, 1]\\n\", \"    final_results[name] = {\\n\", \"        \\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"Precision\\\": precision_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob),\\n\", \"        \\\"PR-AUC\\\": average_precision_score(y_test, y_prob),\\n\", \"    }\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{name}:\\\")\\n\", \"    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=[\\\"No Default\\\", \\\"Default\\\"]))\\n\", \"\\n\", \"results_df = pd.DataFrame(final_results).T\\n\", \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Final Test Results ===\\\")\\n\", \"results_df\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, len(top3), figsize=(5*len(top3), 4))\\n\", \"if len(top3) == 1: axes = [axes]\\n\", \"for ax, (name, model) in zip(axes, top3.items()):\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(y_test, model.predict(X_test_t), ax=ax, cmap=\\\"Blues\\\", display_labels=[\\\"No Default\\\",\\\"Default\\\"])\\n\", \"    ax.set_title(name)\\n\", \"plt.suptitle(\\\"Confusion Matrices — Test Set\\\", y=1.02)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\", \"for name, model in top3.items():\\n\", \"    RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(model, X_test_t, y_test, ax=axes[0], name=name)\\n\", \"    PrecisionRecallDisplay.from_estimator(model, X_test_t, y_test, ax=axes[1], name=name)\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"ROC Curves\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].plot([0,1],[0,1],\\\"k--\\\",alpha=0.5)\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Precision-Recall Curves\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 23. Error Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We examine misclassifications to find patterns.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"best_name = list(top3.keys())[0]\\n\", \"best_model = top3[best_name]\\n\", \"y_pred_best = best_model.predict(X_test_t)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"fn_mask = (y_test == 1) & (y_pred_best == 0)\\n\", \"fp_mask = (y_test == 0) & (y_pred_best == 1)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"False Negatives (missed defaults): {fn_mask.sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"False Positives (false alarms): {fp_mask.sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"FN rate: {fn_mask.sum()/(y_test==1).sum():.1%}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"test_df = X_test.copy()\\n\", \"test_df[\\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"correct\\\"\\n\", \"test_df.loc[fn_mask.values, \\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"false_negative\\\"\\n\", \"test_df.loc[fp_mask.values, \\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"false_positive\\\"\\n\", \"for col in [\\\"LIMIT_BAL\\\", \\\"AGE\\\", \\\"PAY_0\\\"]:\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{col} — mean by error type:\\\")\\n\", \"    print(test_df.groupby(\\\"error_type\\\")[col].mean())\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 24. Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Key findings:**\\n\", \"1. **Payment status (PAY_0)** is the strongest predictor\\n\", \"2. **Credit utilisation** — clients near their limit are higher risk\\n\", \"3. **Payment-to-bill ratio** — consistently paying less than bill amount signals default\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Business recommendations:**\\n\", \"- Monitor PAY_0 monthly and flag accounts with status >= 2\\n\", \"- Alert when utilisation exceeds 80%\\n\", \"- Offer restructured payment plans for declining ratios\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 25. Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Temporal:** 2005 Taiwan data\\n\", \"2. **Geographic:** May not generalise\\n\", \"3. **Features:** Lacks spending categories, income, bureau scores\\n\", \"4. **Undocumented codes:** PAY_x values -2, -1\\n\", \"5. **Static snapshot:** Only 6 months\\n\", \"6. **No cost-sensitive optimisation**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 26. How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Cost-sensitive learning with explicit FN/FP costs\\n\", \"2. Time-series slope features from PAY_x trends\\n\", \"3. Interaction features (credit limit × payment status)\\n\", \"4. Probability calibration\\n\", \"5. Ensemble stacking\\n\", \"6. Threshold tuning via PR curve\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 27. Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- **Fairness:** Audit across SEX, AGE, EDUCATION\\n\", \"- **Monitoring:** Track prediction distribution shifts\\n\", \"- **Explainability:** SHAP for individual explanations\\n\", \"- **Latency:** <10ms scoring\\n\", \"- **Data pipeline:** Automate monthly ingestion\\n\", \"- **A/B testing:** Model interventions vs control\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 28. Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Using accuracy alone with 78% majority class\\n\", \"2. Leaking test data by fitting preprocessors before splitting\\n\", \"3. Treating PAY_x codes as negative delay months\\n\", \"4. Not stratifying with 22% minority\\n\", \"5. Dropping correlated features without domain understanding\\n\", \"6. Overfitting without cross-validation\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 29. Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Find the threshold that maximises F1 on validation set\\n\", \"2. Add SHAP feature importance analysis\\n\", \"3. If FN costs $5,000 and FP costs $200, what is total model cost?\\n\", \"4. Create trend features from PAY_0 to PAY_6\\n\", \"5. Plot calibration curve\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 30. Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Aspect | Detail |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Task** | Binary classification — credit card default |\\n\", \"| **Dataset** | 30,000 clients, 23 features, ~22% default rate |\\n\", \"| **Best metric focus** | F1 and PR-AUC (cost-asymmetric) |\\n\", \"| **Baseline** | DummyClassifier ~78% accuracy, 0% recall |\\n\", \"| **Best models** | Gradient boosting family |\\n\", \"| **Key insight** | PAY_0 is the dominant predictor |\\n\", \"| **Limitation** | Taiwan 2005 data |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**What you learned:**\\n\", \"- How to handle undocumented categorical codes in financial data\\n\", \"- Why accuracy is misleading for imbalanced credit data\\n\", \"- How to engineer payment behaviour ratios\\n\", \"- The full benchmark → AutoML → top 3 evaluation pipeline\"]}\n",
